Interface LIFOQueue<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - type of queue's items.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Stack

    public interface LIFOQueue<E>
    Interface for Lirst-in-First-Out queues.
    Since:
    v. 1.0
    Author:
    Dmitriy Meleshko

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void clear()
      Clears all items of queue.
      E last()
      Works like pop(), but this method returns last element without removing it.
      int length()
      Used for getting size of stack.
      E pop()
      Removes last object from the end.
      void push(E obj)
      Adds object in the end.

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clears all items of queue. Used to make code

        more compact. Now, it will be 
        
 stack.clear();

        Used for getting size of stack.
        Returns:

      • last

        last element.
